<subSubSection id="C36965D095661877FF33B05511AC1E37" pageId="2" pageNumber="25" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCC365B95661877FF33B05513B51CB7" blockId="2.[166,1225,1383,1826]" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">
D i s t r i b u t i o n. 
<emphasis id="B907EA4995661877FE47B05A12BA1C94" bold="true" box="[431,511,1383,1409]" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">
<collectingCountry id="F36476CB95661877FE47B05A12BA1C94" box="[431,511,1383,1409]" name="Russia" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">Russia</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
(district 
<collectingRegion id="49B7F8B995661877FD8FB05A118A1C94" box="[615,719,1383,1409]" country="Russia" name="Sakhalin" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">Sakhalin</collectingRegion>
, Aniva); Japan (Honshu, Kyushu) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24BAA95661877FB8CB05A13A61CB7" author="Moriuti, S." pageId="2" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 30" refId="ref2623" refString="Moriuti, S. 1969. Argyresthiidae of Japan. Bulletin of the University of Osaka Prefecture. Series B, 21, 1 - 30." type="journal article" year="1969">Moriuti, 1969</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCC365B95661877FF33B09512D11F37" blockId="2.[166,1225,1383,1826]" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">
D i a g n o s i s. Wingspan 
<quantity id="4C8B9BBE95661877FDE2B09A11C81CD7" box="[522,653,1447,1474]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" metricValueMax="1.1" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="10.5" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="10.0">10–11 mm</quantity>
. Head and thorax white, dusted with pale greyochreous coloration. Labial palpi pale ochreous. Forewings grey, suffused with dark fuscous dots: a whitish costal spot before apex, and a whitish dorsal streak are diagnostic characters (
<figureCitation id="13482ADE95661877FF46B33A13AE1F34" box="[174,235,1543,1569]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1105,1127]" captionTargetBox="[322,1065,191,1089]" captionTargetId="figure-253@2.[317,1074,174,1089]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 2. Argyresthia communana: 1 — forewing pattern; 2–4 — male genitalia (2 — ventral plate, 3 — valva, 4 — aedeagus); 5 — bursa copulatrix." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414501" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414501/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">fig. 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13482ADE95661877FF1FB33A12401F34" box="[247,261,1543,1569]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[174,207,1408,1430]" captionTargetBox="[325,1069,174,1369]" captionTargetId="figure-159@1.[321,1078,171,1383]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1. Argyresthia kurenzovi: 1 — forewing pattern; 2–4 — male genitalia (2 — ventral view, 3 — ventral plate, 4 — aedeagus); 5 — female genitalia; 6 — bursa copulatrix with signum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414497" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414497/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis id="B907EA4995661877FF1FB33A12401F34" box="[247,261,1543,1569]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">1</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Cilia grey.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCC365B95661877FF33B31A10461F77" blockId="2.[166,1225,1383,1826]" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="13482ADE95661877FE7FB31A11541F54" box="[407,529,1575,1601]" captionStart-0="Fig" captionStart-1="Fig" captionStart-2="Fig" captionStartId-0="2.[166,199,1105,1127]" captionStartId-1="3.[174,207,1063,1085]" captionStartId-2="4.[170,203,990,1012]" captionTargetBox-0="[322,1065,191,1089]" captionTargetBox-1="[334,1055,174,1028]" captionTargetBox-2="[236,1125,179,972]" captionTargetId-0="figure-253@2.[317,1074,174,1089]" captionTargetId-1="figure-291@3.[321,1078,171,1046]" captionTargetId-2="figure-336@4.[232,1167,171,985]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionTargetPageId-2="4" captionText-0="Fig. 2. Argyresthia communana: 1 — forewing pattern; 2–4 — male genitalia (2 — ventral plate, 3 — valva, 4 — aedeagus); 5 — bursa copulatrix." captionText-1="Fig. 3. Paradoxus osyridellus: 1 — moth (habitus, dorsal); 2 — male genitalia (ventral view); 3 — aedeagus; 4 — female genitalia; 5 — bursa copulatrix." captionText-2="Fig. 4. Kessleria saxifragae: 1 — moth (habitus, dorsal); 2 — male genitalia (ventral view); 3 — aedeagus; 4 — female genitalia; 5 — bursa copulatrix." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414501" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414505" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414507" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6414501/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6414505/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/6414507/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">
fig. 2, 
<emphasis id="B907EA4995661877FE0EB31A11541F54" box="[486,529,1575,1601]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">2–4</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Valva nearly of trapezoid shape (
<figureCitation id="13482ADE95661877FC56B31A10BB1F54" box="[958,1022,1575,1601]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1105,1127]" captionTargetBox="[322,1065,191,1089]" captionTargetId="figure-253@2.[317,1074,174,1089]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 2. Argyresthia communana: 1 — forewing pattern; 2–4 — male genitalia (2 — ventral plate, 3 — valva, 4 — aedeagus); 5 — bursa copulatrix." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414501" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414501/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">fig. 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13482ADE95661877FBE5B31A175E1F54" box="[1037,1051,1575,1601]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,1063,1085]" captionTargetBox="[334,1055,174,1028]" captionTargetId="figure-291@3.[321,1078,171,1046]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 3. Paradoxus osyridellus: 1 — moth (habitus, dorsal); 2 — male genitalia (ventral view); 3 — aedeagus; 4 — female genitalia; 5 — bursa copulatrix." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414505/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis id="B907EA4995661877FBE5B31A175E1F54" box="[1037,1051,1575,1601]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">3</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). The arms of ventral plate as long as the length of valva (
<figureCitation id="13482ADE95661877FD74B37A119C1F74" box="[668,729,1607,1633]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1105,1127]" captionTargetBox="[322,1065,191,1089]" captionTargetId="figure-253@2.[317,1074,174,1089]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 2. Argyresthia communana: 1 — forewing pattern; 2–4 — male genitalia (2 — ventral plate, 3 — valva, 4 — aedeagus); 5 — bursa copulatrix." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414501" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414501/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">fig. 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13482ADE95661877FD0DB37A11B61F74" box="[741,755,1607,1633]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[170,203,990,1012]" captionTargetBox="[236,1125,179,972]" captionTargetId="figure-336@4.[232,1167,171,985]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 4. Kessleria saxifragae: 1 — moth (habitus, dorsal); 2 — male genitalia (ventral view); 3 — aedeagus; 4 — female genitalia; 5 — bursa copulatrix." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414507" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414507/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis id="B907EA4995661877FD0DB37A11B61F74" box="[741,755,1607,1633]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">4</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCC365B95661877FF33B35A12D61FB7" blockId="2.[166,1225,1383,1826]" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">
Female genitalia. 
<collectingRegion id="49B7F8B995661877FE41B35512A91F97" box="[425,492,1640,1666]" country="Turkey" name="Bursa" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">Bursa</collectingRegion>
copulatrix with signum in form of a widely spaced sclerotized formation (
<figureCitation id="13482ADE95661877FEC4B3BA122D1FB4" box="[300,360,1671,1697]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,1063,1085]" captionTargetBox="[334,1055,174,1028]" captionTargetId="figure-291@3.[321,1078,171,1046]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 3. Paradoxus osyridellus: 1 — moth (habitus, dorsal); 2 — male genitalia (ventral view); 3 — aedeagus; 4 — female genitalia; 5 — bursa copulatrix." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414505/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">fig. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13482ADE95661877FE9DB3B512C61FB7" box="[373,387,1672,1698]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[174,207,1289,1311]" captionTargetBox="[331,1074,184,1255]" captionTargetId="figure-183@5.[326,1083,166,1269]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 5. Pseudoplutella porrectella: 1 — moth (habitus, dorsal); 2 — male genitalia (lateral view); 3 — aedeagus; 4 — bursa copulatrix." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414511" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414511/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis id="B907EA4995661877FE9DB3B512C61FB7" box="[373,387,1672,1698]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">5</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCC365B95661877FF33B39512DE1E14" blockId="2.[166,1225,1383,1826]" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">
R e m a r k s. Externally resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C734DD895661877FD68B39A108A1FD4" authority="Zell." authorityName="Zell." box="[640,975,1703,1729]" class="Insecta" family="Yponomeutidae" genus="Argyresthia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conjugella">
<emphasis id="B907EA4995661877FD68B39A10CF1FD4" box="[640,906,1703,1729]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">Argyresthia conjugella</emphasis>
Zell.
</taxonomicName>
, but can be readily distinguished from it by the colour of thorax, forewing pattern as well as a shape of valva in the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCC365B95661877FF33B23A11AC1E37" blockId="2.[166,1225,1383,1826]" box="[219,745,1799,1826]" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">
This species was unknown in 
<collectingCountry id="F36476CB95661877FDDEB23A11C71E34" box="[566,642,1799,1825]" name="Russia" pageId="2" pageNumber="25">Russia</collectingCountry>
till now.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
